commit 68e230087aad28a28ec9765978e8fe122d016c96
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 09:12:42 2026 -0400

    refactor(cms)(draft-editor): migrate admin route to DraftEditor, delete inline pipeline

    The /admin/content action shrinks to auth → parse intent → DraftEditor call →
    map result to Response:
    - loader: DraftEditor.load(siteScope) replaces Content.getAdminContent.
    - save-draft / publish: editDocument(siteScope, override) then publish — the
      override is the route's parsed form (assembleOverrides + folded translations).
    - image upload: route validates + stores the raw bytes, then
      applyImageUpload(siteScope, target, key) rewrites the draft.
    - IssueError → issueResponse maps the editor's 400/502 outcomes.

    Subtract (subtract-before-you-add / migrate-callers-then-delete):
    - the duplicated ~165-line inline encode→merge→decode→re-encode→store pipeline
      in admin/content.tsx (both upload and save/publish branches) is gone;
    - Content.getAdminContent (reconciliation) deleted — its callers migrated to
      DraftEditor.load, its tests moved to draft-editor.server.test.ts;
    - the leaked SITE_CONTENT_KEY / SITE_CONTENT_DRAFT_KEY imports + local
      decode/encode codecs + cause-walking issueMessages removed from the route;
    - the now-unused ObjectHead import dropped from content.server.

    Runtime wiring: DraftEditor.layer is layered onto the app BaseLayer via
    provideMerge so it shares the exposed Content (publish busts the public read
    cache) and Storage instances. cms-e2e drives the one service end-to-end against
    the in-memory bucket.

    Runtime proof: dev boots; / /2024 /2026 /team /about + /fr/* render 200 EN+FR;
    authenticated /admin/content loads via the live DraftEditor.load (source:
    defaults, all conferences rendered); save/publish route through the live
    DraftEditor write pipeline (bucketless → 502, identical to pre-branch).

