docs/registration-launch-plan.md:11:| 1 | `reg-launch/draft-editor` | `refactor(cms): DraftEditor absorbs the inline admin write pipeline (scoped key-pairs)` | Cand. 3 | yes (foundation) |
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:23:## Why DraftEditor is Branch 1 (resolves the list-edit-before-DraftEditor churn blocker)
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:25:Both adversarial reviews flagged a `migrate-callers-then-delete` violation: if list-edit ships first, its "Add item → auto-save draft" (settled #10) must call the inline ~165-line write pipeline in `admin/content.tsx`, which a later DraftEditor branch then deletes and rewrites — churning the same call site twice. **Resolution: extract DraftEditor FIRST.** Then list-edit (Branch 2) builds add/remove/reorder on the already-clean `DraftEditor` interface, and is never rewritten. This honors `subtract-before-you-add` (delete the duplication before building on it) and `migrate-callers-then-delete-legacy-apis` (one migration, no parallel pipeline).
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:27:DraftEditor is launch-critical-adjacent: it is the substrate the launch admin work (list-edit) stands on, so it ships in the launch window. It introduces no public-route change, so it carries no runtime-proof obligation beyond the admin e2e test.
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:35:**Module shape — `DraftEditor` (new, `app/lib/content/draft-editor.server.ts`):**
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:42:- **Implementation absorbs:** the ~165 duplicated lines, the double draft-read, the `assembleOverrides`/`collectTranslations`/merge/`decodeDocument`/`encodeDocumentJson` choreography, the per-scope draft/published reconciliation (`load`, moved verbatim from `content.server.ts:484-515`, generalized over `scopeKeys`), and the bucket-key constants. The route action shrinks to "auth → parse intent → call `DraftEditor` → map result to `Response`".
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:44:**Read-path:** `Content.getAdminContent` is replaced by `DraftEditor.load({ kind: 'site' })`; `bust` is parameterized over scope (one cache today; per-scope cache map in Branch 5). The public `getSiteContent` read path is untouched.
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:47:- The duplicated ~165-line inline action body in `admin/content.tsx:138-289` → replaced by `DraftEditor` calls. **Deletion test passes: the inline lines genuinely vanish.**
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:48:- `Content.getAdminContent` (`content.server.ts:484-515`) → moves into `DraftEditor.load` (callers migrated, old method deleted).
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:53:- `cms-e2e.test.ts` — save draft, publish, upload all pass through the one service; route action is auth + `DraftEditor` call only.
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:58:- (1.1) `ContentScope` (single-inhabitant union) + `scopeKeys` + `DraftEditor.load` (reconciliation moved from `getAdminContent`) + tests.
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:59:- (1.2) `DraftEditor.editDocument` + `applyImageUpload` + `publish` + tests (route still calls them; behavior identical).
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:60:- (1.3) Migrate `admin/content.tsx` action to `DraftEditor`, delete the inline ~165-line pipeline + leaked constants.
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:66:**Why second:** every later branch adds list items (hotels, FAQ Q&A, give-directions, form fields). The id-keyed merge is the list-identity foundation. Built on Branch 1's `DraftEditor` (no churn).
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:81:**Admin route (`admin/content.tsx`):** per-list "Add" / "Remove" / reorder controls submitting `intent=list-op`. "Add" appends an empty item with a fresh nanoid and **auto-saves the draft via `DraftEditor.editDocument`** (settled #10 + ADR 0006) so a later photo upload has a server-side target. The action parses ops via `collectListOps`, applies `applyListEdit`, then calls `DraftEditor.editDocument({ kind: 'site' }, merged)` — Branch 1's clean interface, no inline pipeline.
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:98:- (2.3) Admin add/remove/reorder UI + `list-op` action intent (calls `DraftEditor.editDocument`).
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:176:**Resolves codex→claude BLOCKER (forms never CMS-backed) + completeness:** ADR 0008 settles `forms/<form>.json` as first-class storage objects alongside `content/pages/*.json`. **This branch builds BOTH `getPage` AND `getForm` multi-object read paths together** (parallel decode boundary + fallback-to-default + independent cache-bust), so Branch 6's form engine reads CMS-editable form copy, not a hypothetical. The `ContentScope` union (Branch 1) widens here to `{ kind: 'page'; page: PageId } | { kind: 'form'; form: FormId }`, so `DraftEditor` edits any page/form object through the same proven interface.
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:178:**Resolves claude→codex BLOCKER (per-object draft/publish reconciliation):** the single-object draft/published reconciliation (`content.server.ts:484-515`, now `DraftEditor.load` from Branch 1) generalizes over `scopeKeys(scope)` → `{ draftKey, publishedKey }`. Each page/form object gets its **own** `content/pages/<page>.draft.json` + `content/pages/<page>.json` pair (and `forms/<form>.draft.json` + `forms/<form>.json`), its own `head`-compare reconciliation, and its own cache-bust. The admin DraftEditor targets the right object's draft/published pair via its scope. **This was the gap that would have blocked the page publish flow — it is closed by widening Branch 1's already-scoped interface, not by retrofitting.**
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:197:**Admin route:** per-Page `/admin` sections (settled #5), each a `Section` driven by its schema, reusing Branch-2 `ListEdit` for FAQ items / give-directions, writing via `DraftEditor` with the page's scope.
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:208:- (5.2) `ContentScope` widened to page/form; `scopeKeys` gains page/form key-pairs; `DraftEditor.load`/`publish` reconciliation generalized per-object; tests (wiring proven before any route migrates).
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:211:- (5.5) Per-page `/admin` sections (via `DraftEditor` + `ListEdit`).
docs/registration-launch-plan.md:291:1. **Branch 1 (DraftEditor) before Branch 2 (list-edit):** list-edit's auto-save must call a clean write pipeline — extract DraftEditor first or list-edit's action is churned twice (review blocker resolved).
